Enjoyed a tasty lunch at a retro styled Hong Kong cafe in Chinatown, Sydney.

The Fresh Tomato With Pork Chop Baked Spaghetti also had corn, carrots and peas, and melted cheese on top. A nice comfort food type dish.üòã

The Stir Fried Vermicelli With BBQ Pork in XO Sauce was tasty too and not too spicy. 

Also tried the HK style condensed milk tea. Nice and not too sweet.

The servings were very generous. Fun, cool vibe. Liked the fit-out. Felt like I could've been in a cafe in HK.

Haven Signature Daikon Cake featuring House made turnip cake w dried sausage, shrimp, shitake mushroom, charred broccoli, bechamel sauce, xo sauce, confit garlic and radishes.
